ound pale and soft.\n\nThe setting changes to a dark theatrical space. Warm yellow stage lights shine from the right side in a vertical row, creating flares and haze across a mostly black background. The dancer appears in profile under the golden light, still in the same dark burgundy dancewear and pointe shoes. Her face is serious and intent. She opens her chest and lifts her chin slightly, then begins to move with broad, deliberate arm gestures.\n\nShe steps into a larger performance area: a raised black stage with tall pale panels and vertical columns of glowing yellow bulbs on both sides. At times she is seen as a small figure against a large white backdrop; at other moments she is closer, her body silhouetted by the lights. She turns, opens her arms, and travels across the floor on pointe. The stage is minimal and geometric, with glossy dark flooring that reflects her legs and the lights.\n\nShe extends one leg high to the side while balancing on the other, arms spread wide for counterbalance. In another close view, her upper body twists, one arm reaching forward and the other bent behind her, wrists and fingers shaped in expressive ballet lines. Her shoulders, arms, and torso show strength as she transitions through positions. She lowers one arm, lifts the other, and continues moving across the stage, alternating between controlled poses and quick turns.\n\nThe dancer passes in front of the bright yellow bulbs, becoming partly silhouetted in the glare. She brings her arms in toward her body and then opens them again, turning with her head and shoulders leading. Brief closer views show her torso and hips as she pivots; the dark briefs have subtle contrasting trim at the sides. Her pointe shoes skim and tap the black floor as she crosses her legs and rises through her ankles.\n\nIn a wider view, she travels from the back of the stage toward the center with arms lifted. She turns near a glowing vertical light strip, then faces different directions in quick succes